<br>
This is simply wrong. Sorry.  <br>
<br>
Actually hacking into the code in EQ is possible, but it will render the game unplayable most likely.  Monitoring packets to and from the server isn't that difficult.  EQ now uses better encryption, but getting into the log-on server still isn't impossible. And, monitoring interrupt requests sent to the processor from the keyboard will net you the password of the person you are trying to get the password from.  <br>
<br>
It isn't `easy` to do. But it's doable. Stop spreading false information. <p>~Euriped</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umelodist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>melodist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/29/01 5:06:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok, how does one &quot;Hack&quot; an account?</span><hr size=1> /ponder<br>
